message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in South Korea in the past 5 years was the historic summit between North Korean leader Kim Jong-un and South Korean President Moon Jae-in in April 2018. This summit marked the first time a North Korean leader had crossed the border into South Korea since the Korean War in the 1950s. The meeting resulted in the signing of the Panmunjom Declaration, which aimed to improve inter-Korean relations, work towards denuclearization, and establish a lasting peace on the Korean Peninsula. This event was seen as a major step towards reducing tensions and fostering dialogue between the two Koreas.
